@startuml drawer
hide empty description

[*] --> Closed
Closed --> Mounted : request open

state Mounted {
  [*] --> Opening

  Opening : entry / start open animation
  Opening --> Closing : request close
  Opening --> Open : open animation completes

  state Open {
    [*] --> Idle
    Idle --> Tracking : start moving pointer
    Tracking --> Idle : cancel tracking
    Tracking --> Dragging : exceed distance threshold
    Dragging --> Settling : cancel dragging

    state "evaluate drag end" as Evaluate <<choice>>
  
    Dragging --> Evaluate : end drag
    Evaluate --> [*] : [should close]
    note on link
      Drawer should close when both conditions are met:
      1. Either threshold is exceeded:
        - Drag velocity exceeds threshold
        - Drag distance exceeds threshold
      2. No snap point exists further in the closing direction
    end note

    Evaluate --> Settling : [else]

    Settling : entry / start settle animation
    Settling --> Idle : settle animation completes
  }

  note top of Open
    User can interact with the drawer.
  end note

  Open --> Closing : request close
  /' resulting from drag interaction '/
  Open --> Closing 

  Closing : entry / start close animation
  Closing --> [*] : close animation completes
}

Mounted --> Closed

@enduml